I get tired of reading American accounts of American situations. Too
confident, too narrow-minded.

So I went looking for other things.

I found the little bits following this, but haven't looked for corroboration,
and I need to quit soon and go lie down.





ok since i'm posting tonight.. i'll put up this interesting facts?:

The youngest mother on record was just 5 years and 7 months old. She lived in
Lima, Peru and gave birth to a 6?lb baby in 1939 by cesarean section. The
child was raised as her brother until he was 10 when he was told the horrible
truth. She was able to give birth at such a young age due to a hormonal
imbalance.

The world's youngest father was Sean Stewart of Sharnbrook, England. He was
